

~~~ CDR-Stats Requirements ~~~


* Add repository on CentOS 5.4 
--------------------------------
	i386:
		rpm -Uvh http://download.fedora.redhat.com/pub/epel/5/i386/epel-release-5-3.noarch.rpm
		
	x86_64:
		rpm -Uvh http://download.fedora.redhat.com/pub/epel/5/x86_64/epel-release-5-3.noarch.rpm


* Install Git 
---------------
	yum install git


* Install django
------------------
    http://www.djangoproject.com/download/
    
    First, download Django-1.2.1.tar.gz. Then:

        tar xzvf Django-1.2.1.tar.gz
        cd Django-1.2.1
        sudo python setup.py install


* django-debug-toolbar
------------------------
	download :
	git clone http://github.com/robhudson/django-debug-toolbar.git
	
	install :
	cd django-debug-toolbar
	python setup.py bdist
	sudo python setup.py install
	sudo rm -rf build/ dist django_debug_toolbar.egg-info/


* django-dilla
----------------
	To generate Data :
	svn checkout http://django-dilla.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/dilla dilla


* Flot 
-------------
    Flot is a pure Javascript plotting library for jQuery (http://code.google.com/p/flot/)
    
	svn checkout http://flot.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ flot


* EnhanceJS
-------------
    
    http://code.google.com/p/enhancejs/
    this is already included	
	

* django-extensions
-----------------------
	svn checkout http://django-command-extensions.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ django-command-extensions
	then install,
    sudo python setup.py install
    
    # very useful to generate graph :
    

* Extra dependencies 
----------------------
    Jquery
    JqueryUI
    Jquery.dnd
    jquery.contextmenu
    jqdock (http://www.wizzud.com/jqDock/)
    
    




